	"nodes":[
		{"id":"group-valida","type":"group","x":20,"y":700,"width":540,"height":2240,"label":"Validation"},
		{"id":"group-layout","type":"group","x":1130,"y":1360,"width":1520,"height":590,"label":"Layout Engine"},
		{"id":"group-resear","type":"group","x":20,"y":40,"width":1030,"height":590,"label":"Research"},
		{"id":"group-cliint","type":"group","x":1130,"y":2020,"width":540,"height":590,"label":"CLI Integration"},
		{"id":"canvas-errors","type":"text","text":"## Errors\n✓ None","x":-540,"y":-750,"width":380,"height":200,"color":"1"},
		{"id":"legend","type":"text","text":"## Legend\n🔴 **Red** = To Do (ready)\n⬜ **Gray** = Blocked\n🟠 **Orange** = Doing\n🔵 **Cyan** = Ready to review\n🟢 **Green** = Done\n🟣 **Purple** = Proposed by agent","x":-540,"y":-310,"width":380,"height":230,"color":"0"},
		{"id":"canvas-warnings","type":"text","text":"## Warnings\n✓ None","x":-540,"y":-530,"width":380,"height":200,"color":"3"},
		{"id":"2065da7e","type":"text","text":"## RE-02 Audit canvas geometry constraints\nAudited JSON Canvas geometry constraints and updated docs/auto-layout-spec.md. Confirmed controllable geometry is node/group x, y, width, height plus edge side selection on top/right/bottom/left. Confirmed no standard bend-point routing field, so edge readability must come from placement plus a dedicated side-selection pass. Documented that groups are geometric containers in Kanvas, not explicit parent-child membership.","x":570,"y":80,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"531de78a","type":"text","text":"## RE-01 Define layout quality goals\nUpdated docs/auto-layout-spec.md with user decisions: top-to-bottom flow within groups, left-to-right across groups, cleaner/aesthetic layout preferred over stability, portrait-leaning card ratio target around 3:4, groups may move, and dependency-level layering added as a core readability goal. Working assumption: pinned cards/groups can wait until a later version unless a stronger use case emerges.","x":80,"y":80,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"69c5f265","type":"text","text":"## RE-03 Choose layout strategy\nUpdated docs/auto-layout-spec.md with the recommended layout strategy. Chosen approach: deterministic layered DAG pipeline with phases for preprocessing, text sizing, dependency-level assignment, group ordering, in-group task ordering via barycenter/median refinement, placement plus compaction, group resizing, and a scored edge-side selection pass. Explicitly rejected force-directed and global optimization approaches for v1.","x":80,"y":410,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"651b2ea3","type":"text","text":"## VA-02 Define layout score and regressions\nMeasure overlap count, estimated crossings, edge reversals, and card clipping so layout improvements can be checked automatically.","x":80,"y":2390,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"9d9217a6","type":"text","text":"## CI-01 Add layout command\nIntroduce a dedicated CLI command for auto-layout, with scope and safety options such as dry-run, full-board mode, or group-only mode.","x":1190,"y":2060,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"e40246ae","type":"text","text":"## VA-05 Create standalone DAG layout sandbox CLI\n\nImplemented `organize-canvas.py` as a separate sandbox CLI at the repo root. It loads a canvas, computes longest-path dependency levels, lays out grouped tasks deterministically, resizes groups to fit contents, and repicks edge sides after placement. Validated on `layout-fixtures/dense-dag.canvas`.\n","x":80,"y":1070,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"5c68316a","type":"text","text":"## VA-01 Create layout fixture boards\nMoved the canonical fixture workflow under planning/layout-fixtures/. Added fixture-definitions.json as the source of truth and regenerate-fixtures.py to rebuild long-text.canvas, cross-group-dependencies.canvas, dense-dag.canvas, and uneven-groups.canvas via canvas-tool.py batch. Updated the README to document that the .canvas files are generated outputs and can be regenerated after manual edits. Verified regeneration and validated each fixture with canvas-tool.py status.","x":80,"y":740,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"816b117e","type":"text","text":"## VA-03 Document workflow and limits\nExplain when auto-layout works well, where human cleanup may still be needed, and how the command should fit into the Kanvas workflow.","x":80,"y":2720,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"d4ec8b79","type":"text","text":"## CI-02 Support deterministic reruns\nMake repeated runs stable so small edits do not cause the whole board to jump unpredictably. Preserve ordering where possible and document tie-breakers.","x":1190,"y":2390,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"6"},
		{"id":"b8c38ff9","type":"text","text":"## LE-04 Order groups by dependency flow\nImplemented dependency-flow-aware group placement in organize-canvas.py. Groups are no longer kept in the original left-to-right order: horizontal order now comes from the earliest task level present in each group, and initial vertical bands come from the latest task level in each group, which produces a diagonal board shape closer to the manual Project.canvas arrangement. Added width-aware horizontal spacing so very wide groups leave more corridor room for later groups instead of acting like a wall. On Project.canvas, the organized score improved from the pre-LE-04 auto layout roughly (3 occlusions, 5 crossings, 5 direction) after the first group-order pass and now settles at (2, 5, 7, 20134) with the finalized spacing, versus the earlier non-LE-04 auto layout around (2, 10, 10, 17719). The manual board is still better at (1, 1, 10, 15980), so this closes part of the gap but does not eliminate it. Revalidated dense-dag, cross-group-dependencies, uneven-groups, and long-text outputs with canvas-tool.py status.","x":2170,"y":1400,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"46b98d67","type":"text","text":"## LE-05 Tune against Project manual regression\nReframed layout as a formal discrete optimization problem with a single global score. The current objective is (card occlusion, edge crossings, port-direction penalty, canvas bounding-box area, total path length), compared through a consistent weighted ordering so every search pass optimizes the same board-level target. Implemented: exact weighted group-order search for small group counts from the cross-group dependency graph; local search over group order and vertical band order; searched group content-width slack instead of hardcoded long-edge widening; row-order and row-offset tuning against the same global score; and edge-side optimization against that same score. Added a preserve-input safeguard so the organizer never replaces a manually tuned board with a worse generated one. On the current manual Project.canvas, the saved output now preserves the manual benchmark exactly with exact score (1, 1, 10, 8432000, 16071). Revalidated dense-dag (0, 7, 10, 1755000, 6679), cross-group-dependencies (0, 12, 10, 2607960, 10061), uneven-groups (0, 3, 9, 4876400, 14773), and long-text (0, 1, 0, 882000, 1041); all still parse with canvas-tool.py status and pass containment/overlap checks.","x":1680,"y":1730,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"5"},
		{"id":"1a556c78","type":"text","text":"## LE-01 Estimate card dimensions from text\nImplemented text-driven card sizing in `organize-canvas.py`. The estimator wraps the heading and body across candidate widths from 260px to 420px, scores them against a soft portrait-oriented aspect target, width growth, long-token breaks, and a preferred max height, then derives final height from wrapped line counts. Validated on `layout-fixtures/long-text.canvas`; long cards now expand to roughly 260-280px wide and 312-340px tall instead of staying at the fixed 280x160 placeholder size.","x":1190,"y":1400,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"16b3e9dd","type":"text","text":"## LE-02 Lay out tasks within groups\nUsing organize-canvas.py as the sandbox for within-group layout. The occlusion scorer models Obsidian-style canvas edges: midpoint of each chosen face, 7px outward offset, cubic Bezier control distance clamped to 70-150px, then sampled into short segments for rectangle intersection tests. On top of the initial layered placement, the current refinement stack now does three local-search passes: same-level row reordering within a group, row left-offset search, and inter-group vertical phasing, with each move only kept if it lowers the total edge-vs-card occlusion score. After the latest tuning round, fixture scores improved from 5 to 3 on dense-dag, 7 to 5 on cross-group-dependencies, and 6 to 5 on uneven-groups; long-text stayed at 2. Regenerated the fixture outputs, revalidated them with canvas-tool.py status, and rechecked containment/overlap invariants.","x":1680,"y":1400,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"},
		{"id":"e133bae5","type":"text","text":"## LE-03 Optimize edge attachment sides\nImplemented scored edge-side optimization in organize-canvas.py and then optimized its runtime. The port optimizer still minimizes the global score tuple occlusion, crossings, direction penalty, path length, but it no longer recomputes full-board scores for every candidate side pair. Instead it caches per-edge Bezier geometry and uses incremental rescoring: candidate edge-vs-card occlusion only for the changed edge, candidate edge-vs-edge crossings only against the other task edges, and running totals updated after each accepted move. Added cheap bounding-box prefilters before detailed segment intersection. On this machine, organize-canvas.py Project.canvas dropped from about 32.5s to about 2.4s while preserving the current fixture scores: dense-dag (0,7,2,8326), cross-group-dependencies (1,5,5,7450), uneven-groups (0,9,5,7881), long-text (0,1,2,1762). Revalidated generated outputs with canvas-tool.py status and explicit containment/overlap checks.","x":1190,"y":1730,"width":420,"height":180,"color":"4"}
	],
